# Memory Tools

> *Memory is only useful if it's pulled before you need it, not after you've already made the mistake.*

---

## Load — When and What

| Situation | What to Load |
|-----------|-------------|
| `/venom?` | Full: CONTEXT → MEMORY → corrections → ACTIVE → anatomy |
| Vague request | MEMORY.md |
| References past work / decisions | MEMORY.md + corrections.yaml |
| Medium/complex technical task | corrections.yaml + relevant MEMORY section |
| Architecture / strategy | Full load + project.yaml |
| Quick task, clear scope | Skip — execute |

**Proactive rule:** If a project name appears (HvarHub, UNSHELLED, Taxi Arabs, Geolink) → pull relevant MEMORY section before responding. Don't wait to be asked.

---

## The Files

- `.venom/CONTEXT.md` — project brain: who, stack, focus, conventions
- `.venom/memory/MEMORY.md` — cross-session decisions, patterns, corrections
- `.venom/learnings/corrections.yaml` — hard "never do X" — pull before acting in any domain with corrections
- `.venom/learnings/preferences.yaml` — working style, communication preferences
- `.venom/learnings/project.yaml` — project conventions observed
- `.venom/work/ACTIVE.md` — what's in flight

---

## Save — Rules

**Never auto-save without a signal.**

Signals:
- "remember" / "save this" / "keep that"
- `/venom remember: X`
- `/venom learn: [correction|preference|convention] — X`
- Something clearly important just happened → offer: "Want me to remember that?"

When saving:
1. Write to correct file immediately
2. Confirm: "Saved to [file]. [One line of what was captured]."

---

## Recall Protocol

When request references past work or decisions:
1. Read `.venom/memory/MEMORY.md`
2. Read `.venom/learnings/corrections.yaml`
3. Answer from that context — not from scratch

**Don't answer from scratch if memory holds it.**

---

## Work Lifecycle

Temp files created during a session → `.venom/work/[feature]/`
When done → offer: "Ship to docs? Or delete?" Never leave temp files floating.

ACTIVE.md → update when focus shifts. One focus at a time.

---

## Scope Transparency on Memory

If I load CONTEXT but not MEMORY → say so.
If I load MEMORY but not corrections → say so.
If I loaded nothing → say so.

"I loaded CONTEXT and MEMORY. Corrections.yaml not checked — want me to?" is the right pattern.
Looking loaded when I wasn't = the same trust erosion as any other scope gap.
